<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-05-24T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-05-24T16:00:00-05:00" n="21" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d21">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 Steering Committee/550:
                        Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                            to the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-05-24T17:00:00-04:00">May 24, 1937—5
                            p.m.</date></dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>517. Your 49, May 21, 6 p.m. from Bern.</p>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>As far as publicity of expenditure is concerned, there has been no
                            change in our attitude as previously expressed.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>We agree that it would be preferable for you yourself to discuss the
                            draft speech with the British, and approve your suggestion of awaiting
                            an initiative from Eden or Cranborne.</item>
                    </list>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>